{
  "texts": [
    "The effectiveness of these models at each learning opportunity within student assignments were examined to determine when interventions can be most effectively used to help students who can be displaying unproductive persistence.",
    "A study by Kostopoulos et al (2020) assessed the effectiveness of DNN, bagging and boosting for the early prediction of students who are prone to failure.",
    "A variety of features drawn from various educational sources (LMS) are utilized in relation to student's characteristics, academic achievements, and online behavior.",
    "The experimental findings showed that the proposed DL model has decent accuracy with academic attributes; however, it appears to be greater in the early risk prediction of students with economic factors, as it achieved an accuracy of up to 72%.",
    "With the economic background attributes, the accuracy of the bagging classifier was approximately 88%, whereas the accuracy of the boosting classifier was 86%."
  ]
}